Wrestler ‘Macho Man’ Randy Savage Dies in Florida Auto Accident at Age 58

-- B y   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s
-- 
2011-05-20T18:04:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/wrestler-macho-man-randy-savage-dies-in-florida-auto-accident-at-age-58.html
Ralph Poffo, the professional
wrestler known as ‘Macho Man’ Randy Savage, was killed today in
a car crash in Seminole,  Florida .  Poffo, 58, lost control of his vehicle, crossed a concrete
highway median and crashed into a tree at 9:25 a.m., according
to a preliminary report from the Florida Highway Patrol. Poffo
was transported to Largo Medical Center where he later died of
his injuries, the report said.  A second passenger, 56-year-old Barbara Poffo, was
hospitalized with minor injuries. Both were wearing seatbelts
and alcohol is not suspected to have played a role in the
accident, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eben Novy-Williams in New York at 
